    "body": "Initial saturating decode perf numbers, deepseek 64/512 shape and topk length = 2048.\r\n```\r\nVanilla MLA\r\nbatch: 512, seqlen_q: 1, seqlen_k: 16384, nheads: 128, -> 1.98 ms, 1180.70 TFLOPS\r\nDSA, no bitmask (topk selected assumed in bounds)\r\nbatch: 512, seqlen_q: 1, seqlen_k: 16384, nheads: 128, -> 0.31 ms, 955.47 TFLOPS\r\nDSA, bitmask\r\nbatch: 512, seqlen_q: 1, seqlen_k: 16384, nheads: 128, -> 0.33 ms, 898.08 TFLOPS\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow added:\r\n1. persistent kernel for perf ✅ \r\n2. expose through interface ✅\r\n3. handle seqlen_q > seqlen_k when causal (kernel currently hangs) ✅\r\n\r\nTests added in `test_flash_attn_mla_absorbed` and `test_flash_attn_mla_absorbed_varlen`.\r\n\r\ntcgen05 mma codegen is not very good for this kernel, will need to be revised for more perf.\r\n\r\nNot planned in this PR: page table (though high priority), sliding window.\r\n\r\nPR authored by myself and @jack-carlisle-2025",
